I was into anime since I was 9 years old and didn't know they were Japanese animation at all. I have been watching anime for 16 years. I'm like Huuuuuuuuuuuuge fan of manga/anime and I love to watch them in Japanese subs not English dub because the Eng voices annoy the hell out of me. Again I watch animes only in Japanese because their Seiryuus are really brilliant.

I'm beginning to think that people don't realize the anime and manga are the exact same story (except for altered bits in the anime and filler episodes) The manga is the actual, original story. The anime began AFTER the manga was started, therefore ANYTHING that happens in the manga is more canon than what the anime is. I think a lot of people fail to see that the manga is the true story.
